    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-spiced-pollock-stew-with-charred-corn-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to char</p><p>Once done, transfer to a bowl and set aside for later (reserve the pan!) \u2013<strong> </strong>this is your<strong> charred corn</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-spiced-pollock-stew-with-charred-corn-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the corn is charring, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Dissolve your<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> chipotle stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-spiced-pollock-stew-with-charred-corn-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until lightly golden</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-spiced-pollock-stew-with-charred-corn-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has slightly softened, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground coriander</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min until fragrant, then add the <strong>chipotle stock</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5-7 min or until thickened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-spiced-pollock-stew-with-charred-corn-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>remaining ground smoked paprika</strong>,<strong> remaining</strong> <strong>ground coriander</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> black pepper</strong> in a shallow bowl</p><p>Add your<strong> diced pollock </strong>to the bowl and give everything a good mix up until fully coated in the spices \u2013 these are your <strong>spiced diced pollock</strong></p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized diced pollock? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-spiced-pollock-stew-with-charred-corn-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, top with the <strong>spiced diced pollock </strong>and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further or until the fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>Mexican-style spiced pollock stew</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Add the <strong>charred corn</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>to the cooked rice<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>charred corn rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-spiced-pollock-stew-with-charred-corn-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Mexican-style spiced pollock stew</strong> with the <strong>charred corn rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped coriander</strong> and a pinch of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
